# Logic Gates

Logic gates are the basic building blocks of digital circuits. 
They perform logical operations on one or more binary inputs to produce a single output.

## Types of Basic Logic Gates

1. AND Gate  
Output is 1 only when all inputs are 1.

2. OR Gate  
Output is 1 if at least one input is 1.

3. NOT Gate  
It inverts the input signal.

## Universal Gates

1. NAND Gate  
2. NOR Gate  

These gates can be used to implement any logical function.

## Exclusive Gates

1. XOR Gate  
2. XNOR Gate
